==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glyceryl
<hw>Glyc"er*yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Glycer</ets>in + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound radical, <chform>C3H5</chform>, regarded as the
essential radical of glycerin. It is metameric with allyl. Called also
<altname>propenyl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glycide</ent>⟦br⟧
